<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A crew from <ORGANIZATION> CBS-TV </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Rescue 911'' that came to <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION> to film a burglary re-enactment got a first-hand look at real crime. A $ 30,000 camera disappeared Monday night as the crew was unloading equipment to shoot a segment about real-life emergencies. `` It's a sad fact for <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION>,'' said police Lt. <PERSON> Alvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Allcon </PERSON>. `` Here someone is filming a property crime and then they become a victim of a property crime.'' Investigators believe a passer-by simply walked away with the camera that was left unattended on a sidewalk. They have no leads. Filming resumed Monday night after the crew got another camera.
