 at the negotiations on a convention banning chemical weapons and nuclear testing talks and so on. And of course, we will be reporting to you more specifically during the talks and after them. Q: Mr. <PERSON> Shevardnadze </PERSON>, are you going to tell the president that you wish the pace, the progress of U.S.-Soviet relations would quicken? Has he been too cautious? Shevardnadze: Well, I do believe that we have reason to say that the pace of the development of Soviet-American relations has to quicken. That would serve the interest of our two countries, the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION>, and the interests of the world. Thank you.
