<TEXT>
 Former President <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Napoleon </PERSON> <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> is losing his battle with liver cancer and could be near death, his doctors say. `` I thought he was going to die last night -LRB- Tuesday -RRB-. But we were able to stabilize him, and I do n't think he'll die within the next 24 hours,'' said Dr. <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Luis </PERSON> <PERSON> Sacasaid </PERSON> on Wednesday. <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> was in `` serious but stable'' condition Wednesday, the doctor said, but `` Even so, he probably will not recover from this crisis.'' <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON>, 63, led this country for five years until he stepped down June 1 and was <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>'s staunchest ally in the <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hemisphere </LOCATION>. He handed power to elected successor <PERSON> Alfredo </PERSON> <PERSON> Cristiani </PERSON>, of the rightist <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nationalist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>. The cancer was diagnosed in June 1988 in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Walter </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>. Two-thirds of his stomach was removed and chemotherapy was applied to help slow the disease's advance. However, last month the treatment was stopped because <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> was judged too weak to survive its debilitating side-effects. He was bedridden Wednesday at his home in the fashionable <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Benito </LOCATION> neighborhood. A source close to the family said he did not want to be taken to the hospital. <PERSON> Saca </PERSON> said the former president has low blood pressure and difficulty breathing.
