> <PERSON> Miller </PERSON>. `` This is a case about lying to people over television and cheating them out of their money. ... This is a case about fraud.'' Earlier Wednesday, prosecutors wrapped up their case, saying <PERSON> Bakker </PERSON>'s ministry had oversold partnerships at its hotels. The jurors saw 3-year-old tapes of `` The <ORGANIZATION> PTL </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION>'' show in which <PERSON> Bakker </PERSON> called the purchase of such time shares `` a deal of a lifetime.'' `` We're not here to make money,'' <PERSON> Bakker </PERSON> said. `` I hope my critics wake up and realize I'd be a fool if I tried to make money off something like this.''
