<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is a list of some other fatal bus accidents: May 14, 1988 _ Church-owned school bus bursts into flames after colliding with pickup truck being driven by drunk driver on wrong side of Interstate 71 near <LOCATION> Carrollton </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ky. </LOCATION>. Three adults and 24 children are killed Oct. 20, 1987 _ Tractor-trailer crashes into disabled college bus near <LOCATION> Gaffney </LOCATION>, S.C, killing four people and injuring 13. Aug. 28, 1987 _ Truck slams into school bus carrying handicapped children near <LOCATION> Bronson </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, killing six and injuring 17. July 17, 1987 _ Raging floodwaters of the <LOCATION> Guadalupe </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> carry away bus and van carrying 43 people, killing 10 teen-agers from a church camp. May 30, 1986 _ Speeding <ORGANIZATION> Starline </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sightseeing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tours </ORGANIZATION> coach wrecks in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> canyon, killing 21 passengers. The driver was sentenced to four years in prison. May 31, 1985 _ Truck crosses center line and slams into school bus near <LOCATION> Snow </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hill </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION>, killing five children and injuring 20. Jan. 21, 1984 _ High school wrestling team's bus collides with tanker truck near <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Glacier </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mont. </LOCATION>, killing nine people aboard and injuring 19. March 25, 1983 _ Bus carrying school children to a state convention leaves rural road near <LOCATION> Uno </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ark. </LOCATION>, and overturns, killing four students and five teachers. Dec. 24, 1983 _ Bus carrying worshipers to Christmas revival collides with truck near <LOCATION> Devers </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, killing nine people and injuring 14. Nov. 30, 1983 _ <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trail