<HEAD>Returning Tourists Tell of Looting After Hugo</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOAN THOMPSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Weary residents and tourists who arrived here Thursday from <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Croix </LOCATION> said they armed themselves with makeshift weapons and watched in horror as looters rampaged through the hurricane-ravaged island. `` The worst stories that you hear, you can believe them,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Curans </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION>, who was honeymooning with his bride, <PERSON> Patty </PERSON>, when Hurricane Hugo struck. Currans was among 77 people evacuated from the popular tourist retreat by the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> aboard a C-130 transport plane that flew into <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> airport. In Grand Rapids, <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION>, two brothers chartered a plane and rescued their parents after receiving a desperate call from them in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Croix </LOCATION>. `` My father managed to get to a boat yesterday and radioed my brother and _ he only was on for a minute _ he said, ` Do whatever you can to get us out of here,' `` said <PERSON> Kim </PERSON> <PERSON> Sorrelle </PERSON>. `` My parents were in fear for their lives.'' `` My father said it's total anarchy,'' <PERSON> Sorrelle </PERSON> said. `` The island is completely destroyed.'' She said her parents, <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> and <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Langlois </PERSON>, had seen a National Guardsman use his gun to break the lock of a jewelry store for looting, and that people were firing rifles from rooftops. <PERSON> Sorrelle </PERSON>'s two brothers, <PERSON> Joel </PERSON> and <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Langlois </PERSON>, flew to <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> late Wednesday, where they chartered a small plane into <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Croix </LOCATION> on Thursday afternoon. Because their plane had eight seats, the brothers also were bringing four other people back to <LOCATION> Miam