<FIRST>a a PM-ReligionRdp Adv22   09-21 0487</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Religion Rdp, Adv 22,0504</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv22</HEAD>
<HEAD>For release Fri PMs Sept. 22, and thereafter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Vision <ORGANIZATION> Interfaith </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Satellite </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Network </ORGANIZATION>, the year-old venture of a consortium of 22 different faith groups, will expand its hours and add new programs to its faith - and values-oriented schedule beginning Oct. 9 `` We begin our second year with a renewal of our commitment to offer a full range of religious programming,'' said <PERSON> Wil </PERSON> <PERSON> Bane </PERSON>, chief executive of <ORGANIZATION> VISN </ORGANIZATION>, which was started Sept. 19, 1988, by the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Interfaith </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cable </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coalition </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> VISN </ORGANIZATION> will expand its schedule to 18 hours, from 8 a.m. to 2 a.m. Eastern. New programs include `` On The Line,'' a call-in show; `` The Joy of Music,'' discussion and perfomance of classical and sacred music; `` Family Theater;'' `` Short Story Sampler;'' and `` Children's Video Bible.'' Two October specials are <PERSON> Zubin </PERSON> <PERSON> Mehta </PERSON> conducting the Israeli Philharmonic at the ancient fortress <LOCATION> Masada </LOCATION> on Oct. 4 to salute the Jewish New Year, and live coverage Oct. 16 of the `` World Food Day National Conference'' in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Conference </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bishops </ORGANIZATION> will give $ 7.2 million collected in parishes across the country to 213 self-help poverty groups as part of the Campaign for Human Development. `` The funding of these projects, in which low-income people organize to improve their lives, is firmly grounded in the social teachings of the church and in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s traditional concern and compassion for the poorest among us,'' said <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION> Archbishop <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> May </PERSON>, president of the national conference. Since its inception in 1970, the <ORGANIZATION> Campaign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Development </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> the </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> has funded more than 2,500 community-based self-help groups, said the Rev. <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> LoPinto </PERSON>, executive director. `` The issues that concern them most are decent wages and benefits, quality education for their children, affordable housing and drug-free communities.'' The 1989 annual CHD collection in each of the nation's <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> parishes is the weekend of Nov. 18-19.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The American <ORGANIZATION> Jewish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jewish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and Anti-Defamation League will work together toward reversing a `` deterioration'' in communication between the Jewish community and Christian bodies. Citing a `` lack of sensitivity'' by both Christians and Jews to important issues, the three organizations on Sept. 13 announced an agreement to form the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Interreligious </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entity </ORGANIZATION>. They called in a statement for review of <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> `` policies and theological formulations'' seen by Jews as `` erosions of earlier positions that were theologically more forthcoming and politically more sensitive to Jewish concerns.'' They also said Jews need `` a more effective instrumentality that can conduct a wide-ranging dialogue with Christian counterparts.'' `` We hope to advance constructive relations between us and international <ORGANIZATION> Protestant </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> and Christian Orthodox bodies,'' they said. Leadership will be shared by Rabbi <PERSON> Leon </PERSON> <PERSON> Klenicki </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> ADL </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Wyschogrod </PERSON> of the Jewish <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Rabbi </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Rudin </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Jewish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, who will be the first chairman.
</TEXT>
