<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Chase </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Manhattan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the nation's second largest banking company, announced a major recapitalization plan that includes adding $ 1.15 billion to its loan loss reserves to cover shaky Third World debt and the immediate issuance of $ 500 million in new common stock. Chase, which also said Wednesday the plan would result in a loss of more than $ 1 billion in the third quarter, is the second major money-center bank this week to sharply boost its loan loss reserves.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The economy continued to grow late this summer at a slow to moderate pace regionally, while inflation eased across much of the nation, the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> reports. Analysts said Wednesday's report indicates the <ORGANIZATION> Fed </ORGANIZATION> is continuing to attain its goal of a `` soft-landing,'' easing inflationary pressures without slowing the economy so much that it is driven into a recession. In a survey of economic conditions around the country, the central bank said most of its districts `` describe the growth of economic activity as modest or slow, although regional variation in activity is substantial.''
