<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Sales at chain stores have grown faster this year in oil-patch states than elsewhere in the country, while <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> retailers have done better than their <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> rivals, according to a new report. Department stores and discounters in the <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Paso </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, metropolitan area posted the best sales gain for the first half of 1989 while <ORGANIZATION> Akron </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, retailers suffered the worst decline, the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Shopping </ORGANIZATION> centers said in the report released Wednesday.
