 Automakers will phase out some assembly and component plants during the 1990s as they adjust to a shrinking vehicle market, a <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> executive said. None of the closings should hit <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> next year despite a forecast of a 4 percent to 5 percent slump in new vehicle sales, <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Lutz </PERSON>, president of <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, said Wednesday.
