<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> has rejected a plea by Colombian President <PERSON> Virgilio </PERSON> <PERSON> Barco </PERSON> for a one-year reinstatement of a coffee-export quota system that benefitted Colombian farmers, the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> said. Colombian coffee prices have fallen sharply since the 74-nation <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coffee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agreement </ORGANIZATION> _ to which both the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Colombia </LOCATION> belonged _ collapsed in July after the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> pulled out in a dispute over prices with coffee-producing nations.
