<HEAD>SEC, Italian Securities Agency Reach Mutual Assistance Pact</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>'s securities market watchdog have announced a tentative mutal assistance agreement. The announcement Wednesday came in a joint communique issued by <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Ruder </PERSON> and <PERSON> Franco </PERSON> <PERSON> Piga </PERSON>, Chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Commissione </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nazionale </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Per </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> la </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Societa </ORGANIZATION>' e la Borsa -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> CONSOB </ORGANIZATION> -RRB-. The communique covered only the exchange of information between the two agencies. It was issued at the 14th Annual Conference of the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commissions </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Venice </LOCATION>, which <PERSON> Ruder </PERSON> is attending in one of his last official acts before stepping down at the end of the month. The communique was described as `` an interim understanding'' between the two agencies to provide the fullest mutal assistance permitted by law or regulation in their countries to exchange information that will help each agency oversee markets, conduct investigations and prosecute wrongdoers in their own jurisdictions. `` It is in the best interest of all nations to expose and prosecute those who would abuse the integrity of the securities markets,'' the two-page agreement said. It noted that Italian transactions in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> corporate securities grew from about $ 269 million in 1985 to $ 1.8 billion in 1988. Conversely, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> transactions in Italian corporate stock increased from about $ 457 million to some $ 656 million over the same period. Both agencies `` contemplate that it will be a preliminary step to a more expansive and comprehensive memorandum of understanding'' after they obtain the legal authority to do so, the communique said.
