<SECOND>PM-Chase Recap, Bjt,0787</SECOND>
<HEAD>Chase Manhattan Raises Loan-Loss Reseves, Takes Big 3rd Qtr Hit</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By VIVIAN MARINO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Chase </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Manhattan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> has become the second major <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> bank this week to strengthen itself against problem Third World debt, reflecting a growing realization among bankers that the money lent years ago may never be fully repaid. In a major recapitalization plan announced Wednesday, <PERSON> Chase </PERSON> said it would add $ 1.15 billion to its loan-loss reserves in the third quarter and issue $ 500 million in new common stock. The move is expected to result in a loss of more than $ 1 billion in the quarter. <ORGANIZATION> Manufacturers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hanover </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Monday it would add $ 950 million to its reserves and also issue up to $ 500 million in common stock. But unlike <PERSON> Chase </PERSON>, it is raising much-needed capital by selling a controlling interest in its financial services unit, <ORGANIZATION> CIT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>, and a 4.9 percent equity stake to <ORGANIZATION> Dai-Ichi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kangyo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, the world's largest bank, for about $ 1.4 billion. <PERSON> Chase </PERSON> said it would have an after-tax charge totaling $ 1.26 billion in the third quarter, which would result in a net loss of $ 1.12 billion for the period. <PERSON> Chase </PERSON> said it did n't have an earnings estimate for the full year. For the first six months of 1989, <PERSON> Chase </PERSON> earned $ 269 million, or $ 2.57 per share, vs. $ 501 million, or $ 5.53 a share, a year earlier. Included in Chase's after-tax charge is the $ 1.15 billion addition for the loan-loss reserve, an $ 85 million charge reflecting the lower value of problem real estate assets in <LOCATION> Chase </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> banking subsidiary and a $ 25 million charge relating to securities trading activities. `` The basic core earnings of the bank have been going well but they have been masked by these three drags,'' Chairman <PERSON> Willard </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Butcher </PERSON> told a news conference. Butcher said the actions would eliminate a current after-tax earnings drag of about $ 200 million a year. `` This will result in Chase entering the 1990s with renewed financial strength and enhanced earnings potential,'' he said. Chase, with $ 100 billion in assets, is the second largest <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> bank behind <ORGANIZATION> Citicorp </ORGANIZATION>, which has assets of more than $ 210 billion. The Chase announcement came after the close of trading Wednesday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. Chase was up $ 1.62 -LCB- at $ 39.50 a share before trading was halted late in the day. Some industry analysts predicted the market would act favorably to <PERSON> Chase </PERSON>'s actions. `` It's a big step for <PERSON> Chase </PERSON>,'' said <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> McDermott </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Keefe </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bruyette </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Woods </PERSON>. `` By stepping up and taking a big hit and getting the problem into a different zone, it's going to allow for greater focus on its core earnings base.'' With the big charge, <PERSON> Chase </PERSON>'s total reserve for possible credit losses at the end of the third quarter will be about $ 3.7 billion. This includes about $ 2.9 billion for loans to developing nations, or about 46 percent of Chase's total $ 6.2 billion of medium - and long-term loans to Third World countries The ratio had been 26 percent. The major <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> money center banks generally have loan loss reserves equalling roughly a third of their outstanding Third World loans. Chase's new reserve ratio will lead the pack. Major banks have been under increasing pressure lately to boost their reserves to cover Third World debt in the aftermath of the recent <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> debt agreement and the plan by <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Nicholas </PERSON> <PERSON> Brady </PERSON> that emphasizes bank forgiveness of these accounts. `` This action resulted from our ongoing review of economic and political conditions and our belief that recent developments, including the Brady initiative, have resulted in increased pressure on banks to reduce their claims ... and an increased resistance on the part of some lesser developed nations to meet their contractual obligations,'' <PERSON> Butcher </PERSON> said. He said the pressure `` has become apparent in the now-completed <LOCATION> Mexican </LOCATION> negotiations and the negotiating positions announced by other countries.'' Chase's new stock issuance amounts to about 14 million shares. As of June 30, Chase had 90.2 million common shares outstanding. The charge involving the <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> subsidiary reflects the continuing economic downturn in the <LOCATION> Southwest </LOCATION>. By establishing the provision for the real estate loans and foreclosed property, <PERSON> Chase </PERSON> anticipates improvement in the core earnings in that area. After-tax losses for the first half of 1989 for that subsidiary totalled $ 30 million. <PERSON> Chase </PERSON> said it lost $ 25 million after taxes in the first half from securities trading. It said the third-quarter charge reflected its decision to get out of market-making in British government bonds and <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> mortgage-backed securities.
