<HEAD>Amerada Hess Confirms Refinery Damage from Hurricane</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JULIA C. MARTINEZ</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Amerada </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hess </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has confirmed that its big <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Croix </LOCATION> refinery sustained major hurricane damage and will not resume full operations for about 60 days. The company said in a statement after the markets closed Wednesday that `` there had been considerable damage to the plant and to its administrative buildings and employees' housing.'' The <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> company said the refinery, with a capacity of 545,000 barrels a day, would resume partial operations in about 30 days. The refinery supplies markets in the eastern <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>. Reports that there might be major problems at the refinery sent gasoline futures surging Wednesday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. The October contract for unleaded gasoline closed 2.07 cents higher at 59.74 cents a gallon after trading as high as 60.20 cents. Heating oil for October delivery jumped 1.60 cents to 56.55 cents a gallon. Other contract months also had strong gains. An <PERSON> Amerada </PERSON> spokesman said the refinery had been shut down Saturday in preparation for Hurricane Hugo. The refinery had been producing about 400,000 barrels a day of gasoline, distillates and other products, most of which are used in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, said the official, who asked that his name not be used. He said <PERSON> Amerada </PERSON> officials traveled to the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virgin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION> to inspect the refinery earlier in the week but that damage from the hurricane made communication out of <LOCATI