ls. <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> also said a <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> report indicates that the <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Croix </LOCATION> refinery provides only about 50,000 barrels a day of gasoline to <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> markets, while the rest of its production is composed of products such as distillates.
