<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market gained ground today with a lift from fresh evidence of a slowing economy. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 8.93 to 2,692.82 by noontime today on Wall Street. Gainers outnumbered losers by about 9 to 7 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues, with 657 up, 509 down and 619 unchanged. Before the trading day began the <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> reported that the nation's gross national product grew at an annual rate of 2.5 percent, after adjustment for inflation, in the second quarter of the year. That came as a mild surprise to analysts, who had generally been expecting no change in the GNP reading from the 2.7 percent estimated increase the department reported last month. The resulting suggestion of a slower-than-expected pace of business activity prompted a slight decline in open-market interest rates. And brokers said that, in turn, provided a measure of support for stock prices. Chase <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> climbed | to 40 -LRB- in active trading. Wall Streeters generally upgraded their appraisals of the company's earnings outlook following its announcement late Wednesday of large writeoffs on its loans to lesser-developed nations Other money-center bank stocks also rose on the news. <ORGANIZATION> Citicorp </ORGANIZATION> added 1 -LRB- to 32 -LRB-; <ORGANIZATION> J.P. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morgan </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- to 40; <ORGANIZATION> Chemical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Banking </ORGANIZATION> 1 to 39 \, and <ORGANIZATION> Bankamerica </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- to 33 Telerate jumped 5 \ to 20 -RRB- <ORGANIZATION> Dow </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jones </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> proposed to acquire the approximately one-third of <ORGANIZATION> Telerate </ORGANIZATION> it does n't already own for $ 18 a share. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks gained .52 to 192.97. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was up .45 at 379.59. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 67.49 million shares at noontime, against 70.36 million at the same point Wednesday.
