<HEAD>Tender Offer for UAL To Begin Today</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The total cost of an employee-management group's leveraged buyout of <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> would be $ 9.45 billion, according to a merger agreement filed with the <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> The $ 300-a-share tender offer for the parent company of <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> was to begin today. According to the agreement filed with the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION>, the buyout group will require $ 6.8 billion to purchase <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s 22.65 million fully diluted shares. It said the group may refinance $ 950 million in existing <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> debt, which would leave $ 512 million in long-term debt and $ 411 million in capital leases outstanding. In addition, there are fees and a $ 1.3 billion credit facility for working capital included in the total buyout cost. In addition to management personnel and <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> pilots, the buyout group includes <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION> as a minority partner. The group plans to finance the transaction with $ 750 million from <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION>; $ 200 million in voluntary pension contributions from the pilots; $ 1.3 billion from <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> cash reserves and $ 7.2 billion in bank loans. The buyout would give <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> nonmanagement employees 75 percent ownership. Around midday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> was up $ 2.12 -LCB- to $ 287.12 -LCB-.
