<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with close</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices rallied in thin trading late Thursday to close moderately higher. Prices rose on renewed takeover rumors and a healthy showing on Wall Street, which helped to reassure the nervous market. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index, the most closely watched market barometer, closed at 2,380.9, up 11.1 points, or 0.5 percent. The index closed at its session high, rebounding from its low of 2,365.4, which it hit during a brief bout of profit-taking in the morning. Volume was a light 413.8 million shares, down from 513.1 million shares Wednesday. `` The market is still very nervous and volatile,'' a dealer with a large British brokerage said. `` This little bit of takeover talk drew some buying in. But volume is still very thin.''
</TEXT>
