<HEAD>UAL Buyout Cost Could Reach $9.45 Billion</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Texas Air-GM, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The total cost of the <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> buyout could reach $ 9.45 billion, according to <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> filings by the employee-managment group seeking to take over <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>' parent. The group, composed of <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> pilots, <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s top management and <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>, also announced in newspaper ads Thursday the commencement of their tender offer for all outstanding shares of <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s common stock for $ 300 a share. According to the merger agreement filed with the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> on Wednesday, the buyout group will require $ 6.8 billion to purchase <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s 22.65 million fully diluted shares. It said the group may refinance $ 950 million in existing <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> debt, which would leave $ 512 million in long-term debt and $ 411 million in capital leases outstanding. Various fees and a $ 1.3 billion credit facility for working capital are also included in the total buyout cost. The buyout, accepted by <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s board of directors Sept. 14, will give <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> workers 75 percent ownership of the company. Management will own 10 percent and <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> will own 15 percent. The group plans to finance the transaction with $ 750 million from <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION>, $ 200 million in voluntary pension contributions from the pilots, $ 1.3 billion from <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> cash reserves and $ 7.2 billion in bank loans.
