ATION> <ORGANIZATION> Refsnes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION>, said regulators themselves are partially at fault. He said that from 1982 to 1985 `` the regulators just indiscriminately approved bank charters and these banking organizations never had the opportunity to grow in size.'' <PERSON> Rieke </PERSON> predicted it would take five years to clean the slate. <PERSON> Littlefield </PERSON>, who took over as <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> banking commissioner three years ago, said, `` In hindsight, it's easy to make that conclusion: that there were too many banks chartered.''
